<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 01 at 3:49AM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Comanche, southwestern Stephens and northeastern Cotton Counties
through 430 AM CDT...
At 349 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles south of Walters, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Walters, Comanche, Temple, Corum, northwestern Waurika Lake, Empire
City and Hulen.
This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 16 and 19.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
